Edition:
Quote: We have four species of Cyathea in our forests, namely, <i> C. medullaris</i> or pithy; <i>C.dealbata</i> or whitened; <i>C. cunninghamii</i> or Cunningham's; and <i>C. smithii</i> or Smith's. The native names for this genus are Mamaku, Pitau, Korau, and Ponga.
